<subSubSection id="7A470737789D038AECF0385E30EF268A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C369B1C64062CDF02D28065EBCCD40C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F77B1C9EA7EA774E8D7A26123028CE78" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="C0800AEBCEED09C72B27D850A4844193" genus="D." lsidName="D. flavum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="flavum">
<emphasis id="57A200F9F9C9BFB2246F06B3A600C27D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. flavum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C7954EC3B822B70064A97AB164F3A44C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.59874" author="Candolle, AP de" journalOrPublisher="Treuttel &amp; Wuertz, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B6" refString="Candolle, AP de, 1817. Regni vegetabilis systema naturale, sive ordines, genera et species plantarum secundum methodi naturalis normas digestarum et descriptarum. Vol. 1. Treuttel &amp; Wuertz, Paris, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.59874" title="Regni vegetabilis systema naturale, sive ordines, genera et species plantarum secundum methodi naturalis normas digestarum et descriptarum. Vol. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.59874" year="1817">Candolle (1817)</bibRefCitation>
described two varieties (var. 
<taxonomicName id="B9B471C03865473A1A2C8D8F0E5EE69C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Delphinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Delphinium flavum var. velutinum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="flavum" variety="velutinum">Delphinium flavum velutinum</taxonomicName>
and var. 
<taxonomicName id="EAD4159EEC36D24AB0D67F9B4EA41F19" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Delphinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Delphinium flavum var. glabrum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="flavum" variety="glabrum">Delphinium flavum glabrum</taxonomicName>
) based on the pubescence and the bracteole position on the pedicel. We synonymize here 
<taxonomicName id="984B52400ABEA65ED40F11AC33371767" genus="D." lsidName="D. flavum subsp. var. var. velutinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="variety" species="flavum" subSpecies="var." variety="velutinum">D. flavum var. velutinum</taxonomicName>
with the autonym. Candolle indicates that he saw the specimen in 
<normalizedToken id="135D9DCE26746373225BBD8C242ED788" originalValue="Olivier’s">Olivier's</normalizedToken>
herbarium (now at P), whereas we found at G-DC a duplicate received in 1822. At P, we found two sheets of the Olivier and 
<normalizedToken id="51E7F6F9975B6F6D2D3D99241BE63053" originalValue="Bruguière’s">Bruguiere's</normalizedToken>
gathering. It is not sure whether Candolle annotated these sheets. The specimen P00197330 bears the label &quot;dans les lieux incultes steriles de Bagdad a Kermancha&quot; and a mixture of both varieties (the specimen in the bottom right corner corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="FE51A8B3F14B207D4DEFCCF9D7BBE79B" genus="D." lsidName="D. flavum subsp. var. var. glabrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="variety" species="flavum" subSpecies="var." variety="glabrum">D. flavum var. glabrum</taxonomicName>
). We designate as lectotype the six other specimens on this sheet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAC0A6CE58D01DF42182ED8864A08A9C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
A single and fragmentary specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="03039BEF5C0DCA284A409944795E2F35" genus="D." lsidName="D. deserti" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="deserti">
<emphasis id="4715DA944FABF8BE205CDE1C4B795230" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. deserti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, labelled &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="D674201DB625BEC9ED6E5E7C4869AF9E" genus="D." lsidName="D. deserti" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="deserti">D. deserti</taxonomicName>
&quot; by Boissier, was found in G-BOIS (G00788308) and probably came from a P duplicate. We designate as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="11B0980724A33C6078E7EA949AEE1D95" genus="D." lsidName="D. deserti" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="deserti">
<emphasis id="516842977E4A58F78EA1C78F950FF611" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. deserti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the specimen P00197319, the only one bearing a priori an annotation from Boissier.
</paragraph>
